(238, 1, '2013-07-22 18:28:30', '2013-07-22 18:28:30', '<h1>COMMUNITY IMMERSION BETWEEN STARTUP SCHOLARSHIP AND STARTUP PIRATES</h1>\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-198" alt="The Startup Scholarship Logo (WhiteLet+GreyBack) copy copy" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png" /></a>    <a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/StartupPirates_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-197" alt="StartupPirates_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/StartupPirates_a.png" /></a>\r\n\r\nOn this sunny wednesday evolving entrepreneurs from Startup Scholarship met up with the founders and participants of the Startup Pirates program to exchange insights and ideas. The immersion took place in one of the most popular places in Lisbon, Miradouro Sao Pedro de Alcantara. The choice of the location could not be better as the beautiful view of the city is inspiring and the transfer of self-development activities to nature always works out well!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/1013472_523430634391559_1988733873_n2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-206" alt="1013472_523430634391559_1988733873_n" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/1013472_523430634391559_1988733873_n2.jpg" /></a>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\nCreated by the group of friends, Startup Pirates is a concept of one-week events for people with an\r\n\r\nentrepreneurial spirit. The program has a very international character and takes place in many\r\n\r\ncountries all over the world: Portugal, India, Brazil, Poland, etc. It focuses on teaching with a very\r\n\r\npractical approach, pushing you to think outside the box. Pirates stimulate creativity, provide\r\n\r\nbusiness tools to develop participants'' ideas and enable to pitch them in front of <span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">the professional</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;"> </span><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">jury. </span><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">"This week is all about teamwork, critic thought, learning, creativity and </span><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">out-of-the-box thinking".</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStartup Pirates invited some participants from previous edition of the event who shared their\r\n\r\nlessons learnt from best projects expanded during the program. They talked about how much\r\n\r\nthey got support in the development of their concepts and how they evolved from entrepreneurs\r\n\r\nprotective of their business ideas to ones always sharing, discussing and open for the criticism.\r\n\r\nStartup Scholars could discuss specific business ideas and models and ask questions regarding\r\n\r\nany entrepreneurial issues. In the end the Startup Pirates founders admitted how is it to struggle\r\n\r\nwith getting financed and developing a sustainable revenue model for the program like this.\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/935041_523425791058710_504029171_n.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-204" alt="935041_523425791058710_504029171_n" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/935041_523425791058710_504029171_n.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Community immersion: Startup Pirates', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '196-revision-35', '', '', '2013-07-22 18:28:30', '2013-07-22 18:28:30', '', 196, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/196-revision-35/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
