(248, 1, '2013-07-19 13:47:02', '2013-07-19 13:47:02', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EmanuelAlves.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-162" alt="EmanuelAlves" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EmanuelAlves.png" /></a> <a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/LunaCloud_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-163" alt="LunaCloud_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/LunaCloud_a.png" /></a></h3>\r\n<h3>Emanuel "Best of You" Alves</h3>\r\n23. Lisbon, Portugal.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INTERNSHIP:</h3>\r\nBackend developer at Lunacloud.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">IN THE PAST:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">MSc Student''s Representative at FCUL. Member of IT Student''s Commission and the member of organization team of annual event "Informania".</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">IN THE FUTURE:</h3>\r\nHe would like to be working with high tech and make dreams, i.e., businesses, become true. In the short-term, wants to live in NY, London, Paris and Tokyo. In the long-term he will stay in Lisbon to change his country.\r\n<h3>CREATIVITY INSPIRATION:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">NoSQL - a mix between researching and engineering that improves our life (user''s experience of Amazon''s website for example).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WOULD INVEST 1 MILLION $ IN:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">An app mobile to find friends during concerts (without GSM or any kind of fixed infrastructure).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">FAVORITE PLACE ON EARTH:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Home (for now) :)</p>', 'Startup Scholar: Emanuel', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '161-revision-4', '', '', '2013-07-19 13:47:02', '2013-07-19 13:47:02', '', 161, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/161-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(338, 1, '2013-08-01 16:05:34', '2013-08-01 16:05:34', '<h3>"USER EXPERIENCE AND PROTOTYPING" COMMUNITY IMMERSION</h3>\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-198" alt="The Startup Scholarship Logo (WhiteLet+GreyBack) copy copy" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png" /></a><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-276" alt="EntrepreneursBreak_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png" /></a>\r\n\r\nAnother community immersion! This time in "Startup Lisboa" our scholars met with Paulo Fonseca from Entrepreneurs Break-organization led by young entrepreneurial talents and arranging informal startup events aiming at teaching and providing business tools for every wannabe entrepreneur.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-277" alt="IMG_0275" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275-1024x764.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPaulo, the cool and energetic speaker seeming to know everything about designing user experience (UX) in web products, started with drawing the big line between the product and the UX-the user''s feeling coming from using or even just taking a look at a certain product/service. It was quickly highlighted that if we are supposed to pick one thing from the workshop it should be the ability to play the role of the customer, creating users'' stories: "As a... I want... In a way that...".\r\n\r\nThe speaker presented the "bible"-main rules of creating a proper UX. Participants could learn how to get from the early development phase of discovery, through strategy creation, to UX and product design. They also saw some useful tools for basic webpage prototyping: from the old-school paper to digital canvas apps with unlimited options.\r\n\r\nWhat is funny, all together we challenged and analyzed the UX of webpages of some startups that our scholars work with. While putting the critic on one, its CTO suddenly came in and together with 3 interns collaborating on the same project, started debating and defending the validity of their "baby".\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-278" alt="IMG_0271" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271-1024x764.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAbove you can see the logo of Entrepreneurs Break. What is your UX associated with it?:)', 'Community immersion: Entrepreneurs Break', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '275-revision-13', '', '', '2013-08-01 16:05:34', '2013-08-01 16:05:34', '', 275, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/275-revision-13/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(250, 1, '2013-07-25 20:26:51', '2013-07-25 20:26:51', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Mobitto_a.png"><img class=" wp-image-120 alignleft" alt="Mobitto_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Mobitto_a.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>Mobitto</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span style="color: #808080;">EST: June 2011 in UK. 1 year later moved to Lisbon.</span></h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: LOYALTY PROGRAM</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Lets users earn points and rewards at their favorite places.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">HOW?</h3>\r\nMobitto makes loyalty program a game where you can build your own network with friends. It recognizes the places that you may like and proposes the ones that are around you. You earn points for using and sharing experience from specific products services, that later can be exchanged for rewards.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\r\nMobitto was born as a PhD thesis of one of the co-founders, with a clear goal: "Improve the way people interact with their favorite brand and the other way around". In the beginning it was basing on the discount approach but later it shifted towards loyalty &amp; gamification. This was the result of many talks and meetings with (potential) clients, users and team members. The Mobitto team wants to leverage the most powerful marketing tool any marketeer can have: Word of Mouth. They just adapted it to the way people communicate and interact nowadays-through social networks and mobile phones.', 'Startup: Mobitto', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'startup-mobitto', '', '', '2013-07-25 20:26:51', '2013-07-25 20:26:51', '', 0, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/?p=250', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(251, 1, '2013-07-25 17:47:12', '2013-07-25 17:47:12', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/CrowdProcess_a.png"><img alt="CrowdProcess_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/CrowdProcess_a.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>CrowdProcess</h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr">EST: NOVEMBER 2012</h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: DIGITAL SERVICES</h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\n<p dir="ltr">"We''re turning the internet into a SUPERCOMPUTER"</p>\n\n<h3 dir="ltr">HOW?</h3>\nWhile browsing the web, people waste a lot of processing power on their computers. CrowdProcess enables websites to collect tiny amounts of that wasted processing power and turn it into a SINGLE SUPERCOMPUTER that can be used by everyone.\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\n"Our CTO had a huge matrix to process and had no money to buy the infrastructure necessary to do it on Amazon''s AWS. So he started thinking about ways to process that matrix using the processing power of website viewers... so that''s how CrowdProcess was born!"', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '250-revision', '', '', '2013-07-25 17:47:12', '2013-07-25 17:47:12', '', 250, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/250-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
