(270, 1, '2013-07-25 19:34:27', '2013-07-25 19:34:27', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Mobitto_a.png"><img class=" wp-image-120 alignleft" alt="Mobitto_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Mobitto_a.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>Mobitto</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span style="color: #808080;">EST: June 2011 in UK. 1 year later moved to Lisbon.</span></h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: LOYALTY PROGRAM</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Lets users earn points and rewards at their favorite places.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 27px; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif;">HOW?</span></h3>\r\nMobitto makes loyalty program a game where you can build your own network with friends. It recognizes the places that you may like and proposes the ones that are around you. You earn points for using and sharing experience from specific products services, that later can be exchanged for rewards.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\r\nMobitto was born as a PhD thesis of one of the co-founders, with a clear goal: "Improve the way people interact with their favorite brand and the other way around". In the beginning it was basing on the discount approach but later it shifted towards loyalty &amp; gamification. This was the result of many talks and meetings with (potential) clients, users and team members. We want to leverage the most powerful marketing tool any marketeer can have: Word of Mouth. We just adapted it to the way people communicate and interact nowadays, through social networks and mobile phones.\r\n\r\nHaving that said, we didn''t forget the consumers. Nowadays we present ourselves has a universal loyalty app that rewards people for consuming, sharing and recommending the things they like the most. Ever thought you could get paid just for giving your opinion to a friends? Well, now you can...', 