(281, 1, '2013-07-19 13:33:16', '2013-07-19 13:33:16', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Nikos.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-157" alt="Nikos" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Nikos.png" /></a> <a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Prodsmart_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-122" alt="Prodsmart_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Prodsmart_a.png" /></a></h3>\r\n<h3>Nikos "Gangsta''s Paradise" Tzimponis</h3>\r\n22. Thessaloniki, Greece.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INTERNSHIP:</h3>\r\nBusiness development &amp; web sales for Prodsmart.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">IN THE PAST:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Nikos studied Business Administration in Greece. Won some innovational contests about business ideas and innovation, and also had been developing his own project for 1 1/2 years that didn''t ever launched.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">IN THE FUTURE:</h3>\r\nWants to learn more things about start up and to do business with people that want to do business.\r\n<h3>CREATIVITY INSPIRATION:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Actually, he doesn''t have one.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WOULD INVEST 1 MILLION $ IN:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If someone would give me 1 million dollars before I tell him my idea, then my idea would be "give me 1 million and I will not ever return it to you".</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">FAVORITE PLACE ON EARTH:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">My office.</p>', 'Startup Scholar: Nikos Tzimponis', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '156-revision-4', '', '', '2013-07-19 13:33:16', '2013-07-19 13:33:16', '', 156, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/156-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(283, 1, '2013-07-29 20:53:24', '2013-07-29 20:53:24', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Whistle_a1.png"><img class=" wp-image-127 alignleft" alt="Whistle_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Whistle_a1.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>Whistle</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span style="color: #808080;">EST: OCTOBER 2012</span></h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: SERVICE/SOCIAL PLATFORM</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Whistle is a virtual marketplace for services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">HOW?</h3>\r\nThis social platform connects talented people offering simple, day-to-day services with those looking for ones. Whistle lets you filter offers matching required criteria and makes sure you get a response within 24 hours. The payment depends on your satisfaction.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\r\nThe founders where working on something else, when all of the sudden they realized that they were a perfect mix of people with a very specific sort of problems. Catarina is a modern mother with a very busy life and lots of troubles to find quality service providers for her various household needs. Paulo is a freelancer that is always on the lookout to find more clients and generate more business for himself. The combination of these 2 sets of needs lead to the creation of Whistle, an online marketplace for personal and household services where you can find talented and quality service providers nearby.', 'Startup: Whistle', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'startup-whistle', '', '', '2013-07-29 20:53:24', '2013-07-29 20:53:24', '', 0, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/?p=283', 0, 'post', '', 0),
