(319, 1, '2013-08-01 14:52:16', '2013-08-01 14:52:16', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Whistle_a1.png"><img class=" wp-image-127 alignleft" alt="Whistle_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Whistle_a1.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>Whistle</h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span style="color: #808080;">EST: OCTOBER 2012</span></h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: SERVICE/SOCIAL PLATFORM</h3>\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\n<p dir="ltr">Whistle is a virtual marketplace for services.</p>\n\n<h3 dir="ltr">HOW?</h3>\nThis social platform connects talented people offering simple, day-to-day services with those looking for ones. Whistle lets you filter offers matching required criteria and makes sure you get a response within 24 hours. The payment depends on your satisfaction.\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\nThe founders where working on something else, when all of the sudden they realized that they were a perfect mix of people with a very specific sort of problems. Catarina is a modern mother with a very busy life and lots of troubles to find quality service providers for her various household needs. Paulo is a freelancer that is always on the lookout to find more clients and generate more business for himself. The combination of these 2 sets of needs lead to the creation of Whistle, an online marketplace for personal and household services where you can find talented and quality service providers nearby.', 'Startup: Whistle', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '283-autosave', '', '', '2013-08-01 14:52:16', '2013-08-01 14:52:16', '', 283, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/283-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
