(327, 1, '2013-08-01 15:41:48', '2013-08-01 15:41:48', '<h3>"USER EXPERIENCE AND PROTOTYPING" COMMUNITY IMMERSION</h3>\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-198" alt="The Startup Scholarship Logo (WhiteLet+GreyBack) copy copy" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png" /></a><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-276" alt="EntrepreneursBreak_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png" /></a>\r\n\r\nAnother community immersion! This time in "Startup Lisboa" our scholars met with Paulo Fonseca from Entrepreneurs Break-organization led by young entrepreneurial talents and arranging informal startup events aiming at teaching and providing business tools for every wannabe entrepreneur.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-277" alt="IMG_0275" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275-1024x764.jpg" /></a>Paulo, the cool and energetic speaker seeming to know everything about designing user experience (UX) in web products, started with drawing the big line between the product and the UX-the user''s feeling coming from using or even just taking a look at certain product/service. It was quickly highlighted that if participants are supposed to pick one thing from the workshop it should be the ability to play the role of the customer, creating users'' stories: "As a... I want... In a way that..."\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-278" alt="IMG_0271" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271-1024x764.jpg" /></a>kpkpkpkpk\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Community immersion: Entrepreneurs Break', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '275-revision-5', '', '', '2013-08-01 15:41:48', '2013-08-01 15:41:48', '', 275, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/275-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(328, 1, '2013-08-01 15:54:47', '2013-08-01 15:54:47', '<h3>"USER EXPERIENCE AND PROTOTYPING" COMMUNITY IMMERSION</h3>\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-198" alt="The Startup Scholarship Logo (WhiteLet+GreyBack) copy copy" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png" /></a><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-276" alt="EntrepreneursBreak_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png" /></a>\r\n\r\nAnother community immersion! This time in "Startup Lisboa" our scholars met with Paulo Fonseca from Entrepreneurs Break-organization led by young entrepreneurial talents and arranging informal startup events aiming at teaching and providing business tools for every wannabe entrepreneur.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-277" alt="IMG_0275" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275-1024x764.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\nPaulo, the cool and energetic speaker seeming to know everything about designing user experience (UX) in web products, started with drawing the big line between the product and the UX-the user''s feeling coming from using or even just taking a look at certain product/service. It was quickly highlighted that if we are supposed to pick one thing from the workshop it should be the ability to play the role of the customer, creating users'' stories: "As a... I want... In a way that...".\r\n\r\nParticipants could learn how to get from the phase of discovery, through strategy creation, to UX and product design.\r\n\r\nWhat is funny, all together we challenged and analyzed the UX of webpages of some startups that our scholars work with. While putting the critic on one, its CTO suddenly came in and together with 3 interns collaborating on the same project, started debating and defending the validity of their "baby".\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-278" alt="IMG_0271" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271-1024x764.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Community immersion: Entrepreneurs Break', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '275-revision-6', '', '', '2013-08-01 15:54:47', '2013-08-01 15:54:47', '', 275, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/275-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(329, 1, '2013-08-01 16:01:16', '2013-08-01 16:01:16', '<h3>"USER EXPERIENCE AND PROTOTYPING" COMMUNITY IMMERSION</h3>\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-198" alt="The Startup Scholarship Logo (WhiteLet+GreyBack) copy copy" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/The-Startup-Scholarship-Logo-WhiteLet+GreyBack-copy-copy.png" /></a><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-276" alt="EntrepreneursBreak_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/EntrepreneursBreak_a.png" /></a>\r\n\r\nAnother community immersion! This time in "Startup Lisboa" our scholars met with Paulo Fonseca from Entrepreneurs Break-organization led by young entrepreneurial talents and arranging informal startup events aiming at teaching and providing business tools for every wannabe entrepreneur.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-277" alt="IMG_0275" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0275-1024x764.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\nPaulo, the cool and energetic speaker seeming to know everything about designing user experience (UX) in web products, started with drawing the big line between the product and the UX-the user''s feeling coming from using or even just taking a look at certain product/service. It was quickly highlighted that if we are supposed to pick one thing from the workshop it should be the ability to play the role of the customer, creating users'' stories: "As a... I want... In a way that...".\r\n\r\nThe speaker presented the "bible"-main rules of creating a proper UX. Participants could learn how to get from the early development phase of discovery, through strategy creation, to UX and product design. They also saw some useful tools for basic webpage prototyping: from the old-school paper to digital canvas apps with unlimited options.\r\n\r\nWhat is funny, all together we challenged and analyzed the UX of webpages of some startups that our scholars work with. While putting the critic on one, its CTO suddenly came in and together with 3 interns collaborating on the same project, started debating and defending the validity of their "baby".\r\n\r\n<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-278" alt="IMG_0271" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0271-1024x764.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\nAbove you can see the logo of Entrepreneurs Break. What is your UX associated with them?:)', 'Community immersion: Entrepreneurs Break', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '275-revision-7', '', '', '2013-08-01 16:01:16', '2013-08-01 16:01:16', '', 275, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/275-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
