(335, 1, '2013-08-01 15:24:39', '2013-08-01 15:24:39', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/TableAndFriends_a.png"><img class="alignleft" alt="TableAndFriends_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/TableAndFriends_a.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>Table &amp; Friends</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">EST: FEBRUARY 2012</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: SERVICE/SOCIAL PLATFORM</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Lets you and your friends book a dinner in a perfect place.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">HOW?</h3>\r\nTable &amp; Friends aims to put together the benefits of the social web with a vast array of restaurants in several countries. The platform lets users book an event in the most suitable location, contact with guests and negotiate discounts.\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\r\n"It all started when i was at a dinner table with another 3 people when we should have been 10-12. All because of the lack of communication"- Andre Lopes, founder.', 'Startup: Table & Friends', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '318-revision-6', '', '', '2013-08-01 15:24:39', '2013-08-01 15:24:39', '', 318, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/318-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
