(358, 1, '2013-08-12 19:21:17', '2013-08-12 19:21:17', '<h3><a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/LunaCloud_a.png"><img class=" wp-image-163 alignleft" alt="LunaCloud_a" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/LunaCloud_a.png" width="137" height="137" /></a>Lunacloud</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">EST: OCTOBER 2011</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">INDUSTRY: CLOUD COMPUTING</h3>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">WHAT?</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Lunacloud is a service providing cloud hosting for companies.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">HOW?</h3>\r\nIt delivers easy-to-use solutions in the areas of cloud servers, storage and databases. Everything''s simple, cheap and with high performance. "We want to Lunacloud to be the most global of the local cloud service providers, competitive in pricing, simple to use. And sexy."\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">THE ORIGIN OF THE IDEA:</h3>\r\nIn the past, the CEO António Miguel Ferreira has founded other internet businesses- Esoterica and Amen. When it comes to cloud infrastructure industry he felt that the existing offers, mainly from the market leader Amazon, lacked three main things: simplicity, low price and local accessibility. Therefore, basing on the past experience and the existing market gap, the team decided to launch Lunacloud.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Startup: Lunacloud', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'startup-lunacloud', '', '', '2013-08-12 19:21:17', '2013-08-12 19:21:17', '', 0, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/?p=358', 0, 'post', '', 0),
