(436, 1, '2013-09-04 14:33:18', '2013-09-04 14:33:18', '<a href="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Rui_Costa1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-409" alt="Rui_Costa1" src="http://startupscholarship.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/Rui_Costa1.png" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRui has a Master''s degree in Networks and Communications Engineering by Instituto Superior Técnico (IST), of the Technical University of Lisbon, having as main research and thesis topic Vehicular Ad-hoc Networks and Intelligent Transportation Systems. Currently works as Systems Engineer at Veniam Works, developing cutting edge communication systems and architectures for vehicular-oriented applications and services.\r\n\r\nServing has a very active volunteer for IEEE, Rui started as a Vice-Chair for Technical Activities in his university student-branch, and currently positioned in several committees as University Activities Coordinator for Region 8 (Europe, Middle-East and Africa) and member of the Student Educational Resources Committee of the IEEE EAB (Educational Activities Board).\r\n\r\nBeing a creative presenter, had led talks about topics such as, team management and motivation, technological trends of education, entrepreneurship and creativity, along with several other technical talks about his research field of interest.\r\n\r\nRui is the founder and coordinator of IEEE Academic, a innovative multilingual online educational resource that offers an easy-to-use, free accessible, online platform with locally-focused multimedia contents in several fields of education.\r\n\r\nHe gave to our scholars a workshop on Bootstrap and Responsive Design.\r\n\r\nYou can follow him on Twitter at <a href="https://twitter.com/ruicostatwit" target="_blank">@ruicostatwit</a>.', 'Thank You Post: Rui Costa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'thank-you-post-rui-costa', '', '', '2013-09-04 14:33:18', '2013-09-04 14:33:18', '', 0, 'http://startupscholarship.org/blog/?p=436', 0, 'post', '', 0),
